        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 4:36PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 436 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Taylorsville, or near Bethlehem, moving north at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Little River In Alexander County, Bethlehem, Millersville, Ellendale,
Taylorsville, Vashti, Hiddenite, Lake Hickory, and Kings Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
